.ds n) explain_select_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_select_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_select_or_die \- blah blah and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_select_or_die(3)" \
    "blah blah and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/select.h>
.sp 0.3
void explain_select_or_die(int nfds, fd_set *readfds, fd_set *writefds,
fd_set *exceptfds, struct timeval *timeout);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_select_or_die\fP function
is used to call the \f[I]select\fP(2) system
call.  On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP,
obtained from \f[I]explain_select\fP(3),
and then the process terminates
by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
This function is intended to be used in a fashion
similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
explain_select_or_die(nfds, readfds, writefds, exceptfds, timeout);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
.TP 8n
\f[I]nfds\fP
The nfds, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]select\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]readfds\fP
The readfds, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]select\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]writefds\fP
The writefds, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]select\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]exceptfds\fP
The exceptfds, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]select\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]timeout\fP
The timeout, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]select\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
This function only returns on success.
On failure, prints an explanation and exits.
